---
import Layout from '../../components/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Agent Memory Use Case — Pay-per-call vector store for agent runtimes"
  description="Add persistent semantic memory to any agent: MemoryServe ($0.001/op) + EmbedPay ($0.00005/1k tokens). Per-agent isolation, GDPR-compliant deletion, no signup, x402 USDC on Base."
  breadcrumbs={[{ name: 'Use cases', url: 'https://agents.melis.ai/use-cases/agent-memory' }, { name: 'Agent memory', url: 'https://agents.melis.ai/use-cases/agent-memory' }]}
>
  <div class="container doc-page">
    <div class="doc-header">
      <h1>Use case: agent memory</h1>
      <p class="doc-sub">
        Persistent, semantic, per-agent memory with no signup and no infra to provision.
      </p>
    </div>

    <section>
      <h2>The problem</h2>
      <p>
        Most agent runtimes lose context between sessions. Adding persistent memory means
        either provisioning a vector database (Pinecone, Qdrant Cloud, Weaviate), wiring an
        embeddings provider (OpenAI account + key), and managing per-tenant isolation — or
        accepting goldfish-memory agents.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>The composition</h2>
      <pre><code>{`# Write
POST embedpay.melis.ai/embed   {"input": "<text>"}  →  vector (1536d)
POST memoryserve.melis.ai/memory/write
     {"agent_id": "<id>", "content": "<text>", "vector": <...>}

# Recall
POST embedpay.melis.ai/embed   {"input": "<query>"}  →  vector
POST memoryserve.melis.ai/memory/query
     {"agent_id": "<id>", "vector": <...>, "top_k": 5}
   →  list of {content, score, tags, created_at}

# Optional: scrub each retrieved chunk before LLM injection
POST memscrub.melis.ai/scrub   {"content": "<chunk>"}  →  risk_score`}</code></pre>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>The cost</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Write: ~$0.0013 per memory ($0.0003 EmbedPay + $0.001 MemoryServe)</li>
        <li>Query: ~$0.0023 per recall ($0.0003 EmbedPay + $0.001 MemoryServe + $0.001 MEMSCRUB on each retrieved chunk)</li>
        <li>Bring your own vector and skip EmbedPay: cost drops to $0.001 (write) and $0.002 (query+scrub)</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Why melis</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Per-agent isolation via <code>agent_id</code> — no shared index, no leakage between tenants</li>
        <li>Free GDPR delete: <code>DELETE /memory/agent/{`{id}`}</code> wipes everything for an agent</li>
        <li>BYO vector option — drop EmbedPay if you already have an embedding</li>
        <li>MEMSCRUB gates retrieved chunks against indirect prompt injection — important for agent runtimes that ingest untrusted content</li>
        <li>No signup, no API key, no infra. Wallet address is the identity.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Related</h2>
      <p>
        <a href="/pipelines/rag">Canonical RAG pipeline</a> · <a href="/services/memoryserve">MemoryServe</a> ·
        <a href="/services/embedpay">EmbedPay</a> · <a href="/services/memscrub">MEMSCRUB</a> ·
        <a href="/comparison/vs-pinecone">vs Pinecone</a>
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>

  <style>
    .doc-page { padding-top: 4rem; padding-bottom: 5rem; max-width: 800px; }
    .doc-header { margin-bottom: 3rem; }
    h1 { font-size: 2rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
    .doc-sub { color: var(--text-2); font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.7; max-width: 720px; }
    section { margin-bottom: 2.25rem; }
    section h2 { font-size: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
    section p, section li { color: var(--text-2); line-height: 1.7; font-size: 15px; }
    section ul { padding-left: 1.25rem; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.5rem; }
    pre { font-size: 13px; }
  </style>
</Layout>
